Step 1 Update or install python3.7 ( no need for this step if you have python3.6 installed )
- to update follow this link -> https://www.itsupportwale.com/blog/how-to-upgrade-to-python-3-7-on-ubuntu-18-10/
- to install follow this link -> https://phoenixnap.com/kb/how-to-install-python-3-ubuntu

Step 2 Install django inside virtual env and also to install virtual env 
- go to this link and install using pip -> https://hostadvice.com/how-to/how-to-install-django-on-ubuntu-16/
- NOTE: Install django==2.2

Step 3 Install
- sudo apt-get install build-esssential python3.7-dev(python3.6-dev if you have python3.6)

Step 4 Install following in your virtual environment
- pip3 install django==2.2
- pip3 install cryptography
- pip3 install djangosaml2idp
- pip3 install pysaml2
